commentTextItems.html: cut away in front of point and it goes to the rope, Ireland win the game and the series.

commentPostTextItems.html: Ireland made that a bit more tricky than it had to be by losing cheap wickets but they got home in the end with three wickets to spare.
Kevin O'Brien's knock was crucial in the chase aided by Thompson and finished off by Mooney.
The final game of the series takes place on Friday where Scotland will search for consolation and Ireland, the whitewash.
Ryan Bailey's report of the day should be up soon but from me Conor Hayes in a sunny Malahide, it's goodbye.

commentTextItems.html: too short and down leg side, scores are level
short one and he misses with the pull shot
fantastic reverse sweep from Mooney which lobs the fielders and flies to the rope
forward defensive played to that delivery
comes down the pitch but can only tap it towards first slip
thinks about a pull but eventually leaves it
turned behind square and an easy two nearly turns into a run out as they stroll the first one
steered to a short mid wicket
brilliant straight drive by Sorensen, Davey looks perplexed
punched towards mid-off and two misfields in the offside mean it's a boundary
turned towards the boundary at cow corner for a couple
quick single taken to mid-on this time

milestones.description: Berrington and Evans's 48-run partnership is SCOT's highest for the 9th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 44 between Sharif and Mommsen
Kevin O'Brien has scored 12 fifty-plus scores in ODIs, the most for IRE breaking Porterfield's record
Craig Young has taken the most five-wicket hauls (1) in ODIs for IRE, going past vd Merwe's record
Josh Davey has taken the most five-wicket hauls (1) in ODIs for SCOT, going past Gordon Goudie's record

stories.title: Ireland take series after late wobble
stories.subTitle: Ireland v Scotland, 2nd ODI, Malahide
stories.seoTitle: Ireland take series after late wobble
stories.summary: Ireland secured the one-day series but they were made to work for their three-wicket win, firstly by a fine hundred from Richie Berrington and then a late push by Scotland in the field
